                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d414">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.51A/1143: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ford</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-05-24T16:00:00+03:25"
                            >May 24, 1944—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received May 24—2:08 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>366. My 359 May 22. Millspaugh and I both feel that note suggested in
                    Department’s 303 May 17, should be presented at once before he and I have our
                    next interview together with Prime Minister. I hope therefore Department will
                    telegraph authorization urgently.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Ford</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
